The paper deals with compressed sensing and signal reconstruction, which are core topics in information theory (cs.IT) and signal processing (cs.SP). The use of partial support information also suggests a potential connection to machine learning (cs.LG), where similar techniques are used for sparse signal recovery. The numerical experiments on audio and video signals suggest a potential connection to multimedia (cs.MM) and computer vision (cs.CV).
